					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">BIT # works only on CMOS chips, such as those in the Lynx, TG16, Super NES, Apple IIc and IIGS, and late Apple IIe. On the original 6502, seen in Atari 2600/5200/7800, Commodore 64, Apple II/II+/III/IIe, and NES, BIT # is a 2-byte no-op.</div>

